<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="405" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1668,2020]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,395]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="405" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1995,2020]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Comments</emphasis>
. The species is characterized by rather long flagellomeres (l/w index of 2.4), a long palpus, lack of macrotrichia on CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[386,394,166,180]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">2</subScript>
, a broad tibial comb, toothless claws, slender gonostylus with a short apical tooth and 3 equal spines at the base of the tooth, a small and rounded tegmen, and a long aedeagus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,395]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">
The slide of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hardy" authorityName="Hardy" box="[347,579,226,251]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Sciara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aliena">
<emphasis box="[347,499,227,251]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Sciara aliena</emphasis>
Hardy
</taxonomicName>
is the 
<typeStatus box="[661,759,226,251]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">holotype</typeStatus>
for 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hardy)" baseAuthorityName="Hardy" box="[810,1197,226,251]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Austrosciara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hawaiiensis">
<emphasis box="[810,1095,227,251]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Austrosciara hawaiiensis</emphasis>
(Hardy)
</taxonomicName>
. It seems that Hardy initially decided on the name 
<taxonomicName box="[482,552,263,287]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Sciara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aliena">
<emphasis box="[482,552,263,287]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">aliena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but subsequently published the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mohrig &amp; Kauschke &amp; Broadley" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Mohrig &amp; Kauschke &amp; Broadley" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[979,1111,263,287]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Austrosciara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hawaiiensis">
<emphasis box="[979,1111,263,287]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">hawaiiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and neglected to change the label on the slide. The slide (No. 2491) corresponds to the same in the description on page 80 of 
<bibRefCitation author="Hardy, D. E." box="[1237,1388,298,323]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" pagination="72 - 90" refId="ref15081" refString="Hardy, D. E. (1956) New Hawaiian Sciaridae (Diptera). Proceedings of the Hawaiian Entomological Society, 16 (1), 72 - 90." type="journal article" year="1956">Hardy (1956)</bibRefCitation>
and in the catalog by 
<bibRefCitation author="Steffan, W. A." box="[344,508,334,359]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" pagination="47 - 50" refId="ref17917" refString="Steffan, W. A. (1976) Catalog of entomological types in the Bernice P. Bishop Museum. Diptera: Sciaridae. Pacific Insects, 17 (1), 47 - 50." type="journal article" year="1976">Steffan (1976)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
